      • getKeyField

        public String getKeyField()
        Description copied from interface: ChartDataSet
        Can be null. If set, the ChartService will try to use it to add series to the chart. For example, when data from 2 sensors is in the table, the key field can be the idSensor, and the ChartService will use this information to plot data from 1 sensor as red, and the other as green. Check XYChart or BarsChart (update method) and createCategories method in order to implement your own ChartService
        Specified by:
        getKeyField in interface ChartDataSet
        Returns:
        the key field

      • getDomainField

        public String getDomainField()
        Description copied from interface: ChartDataSet
        Values of the domain field will be used as X axis in XYPlot, for example or as Domain axis in CategoryPlot. Values can be numeric, time, string... If String, the user must choose a CategoryPlot. For example, years, months, or position ID will be suitable values
        Specified by:
